08</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">38923692</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Lee S. M., Yoon S. J., Park K. W., et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Semantic Variant Primary Progressive Aphasia With ANXA11 p.D40G,&#x201d; Alzheimer's &amp; Dementia 21, no. 3 (2025): e14566.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC11881632</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">40042459</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Faber R., &#x201c;Frontotemporal Lobar Degeneration: A Consensus on Clinical Diagnostic Criteria,&#x201d; Neurology 53, no. 5 (1999): 1159.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">10496296</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Lecona E., Turnay J., Olmo N., et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Structural and Functional Characterization of Recombinant Mouse Annexin A11: Influence of Calcium Binding,&#x201d; Biochemical Journal 373, no. Pt 2 (2003): 437&#x2013;449.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC1223495</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">12689336</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Benz J. and Hofmann A., &#x201c;Annexins: From Structure to Function,&#x201d; Biological Chemistry 378, no. 3&#x2013;4 (1997): 177&#x2013;183.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">9165068</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Fernandopulle M., Wang G. Z., Nixon&#x2010;Abell J., et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Inherited and Sporadic Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis and Fronto&#x2010;Temporal Lobar Degenerations Arising From Pathological Condensates of Phase Separating Proteins,&#x201d; Human Molecular Genetics 28, no. R2 (2019): R187&#x2013;R196.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC6872449</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">31595953</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Arseni D., Nonaka T., Jacobsen M. H., et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Heteromeric Amyloid Filaments of ANXA11 and TDP&#x2010;43 in FTLD&#x